Source: argeo-tp-bootstrap
Section: unknown
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Mathieu Baudier <mbaudier@argeo.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), openjdk-17-jdk
Standards-Version: 4.5.1
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: argeo-tp-log
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Argeo third party logging APIs
 SLF4J and Commons Logging APIs redirecting to Java System.Logger

Package: argeo-tp-log-source
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Argeo third party logging APIs (source files)
 Source code packaged as jar files usable in an Eclipse target platform.

Package: argeo-tp-build
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, argeo-tp-log
Description: Argeo Build third party libraries
 Eclipse ECJ compiler and BND library.

Package: argeo-tp-build-source
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Argeo Build third party libraries (source files)
 Source code packaged as jar files usable in an Eclipse target platform.

Package: argeo-build-scripts
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, argeo-tp-build
Description: Argeo Build scripts and files to include
 The version of Argeo Build which was used to bootstrap the platform.
 While Argeo Build is rather supposed to be included in the sources of
 a given layer as a git submodule, this package allows predictable and
 reproducible builds if needed.
